inout.indexing

Class Indexing<V extends java.lang.Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • inout.indexing.Indexing<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BinaryIndexing, HexadecimalIndexing

    public class Indexing<V extends java.lang.Number>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Indexing is a class to store n-gram frequencies and probabilites in a more efficient manner.

    Normally, it would be stored in a format like

    word 1 word 2 ... word n value

    However, this makes the amount of disk space needed even bigger. Therefore, each word is given a unique ID instead. The ID can then be looked up in a lexicon.

    Author:
    Dennis Ulmer

    Serialized Form
